    "text_3": {
      "type": "content-block",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_1": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "The Cultural Convergence: What Inspired the Collection?",
            "tag": "h2",
            "size": "h3",
            "font": "serif"
          }
        },
        "text_1": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>The <em>Rolling Links</em> collection is more than just a fashion statement; it's a celebration of the unexpected crossover between golf and skateboarding. At the heart of this collaboration is the shared ethos of both sports. Golf and skateboarding, though different in many ways, both emphasise self-expression and community, where individuality is at the forefront of the experience.</p><p>Adam Brown, senior brand director at adidas Skateboarding, highlights this connection: \u201cThis type of collaboration at adidas is just one that makes sense, especially since there are so many parallels between the two sports. We see the changes that are happening in golf from a style standpoint, and we\u2019re excited to partner with the golf team on something unique for the course that has a skate influence.\u201d</p><p>The result is a collection that disrupts traditional golf attire, introducing elements of skate culture into a space that has historically been more formal. Yet, this is no mere trend for trend\u2019s sake. The collaboration taps into the organic interest skateboarders have shown in golf, offering them apparel that allows for self-expression both on the green and off.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
