    "text_4": {
      "type": "content-block",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_1": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Pushing the Boundaries of Golf Fashion",
            "tag": "h2",
            "size": "h3",
            "font": "serif"
          }
        },
        "text_1": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>The <em>Rolling Links</em> collection also signals a broader shift in golf fashion. As Dylan Moore, creative director of adidas Golf, points out: \u201cThe golf fashion landscape today is getting influenced by numerous areas across sport, culture, and fashion. Like golf, skateboarding is a sport where style is unassuming, individual, and with a little bit of attitude. We saw an opportunity to bring some of that design direction from our skateboarding counterparts at the brand to create something truly unique for the course and continue to push golf fashion in a new way.\u201d</p><p>This collection is not just about merging skate and golf styles - it\u2019s about challenging the traditional norms of golf fashion. By incorporating skateboarding\u2019s casual, unorthodox attitude into the more formal, rule-bound world of golf, adidas is making a bold statement: golf fashion can be as individualistic and expressive as skate culture, and it\u2019s time for it to evolve.</p><h2></h2><h2><strong>The Appeal of Palm Springs: A Laid-Back Vibe</strong></h2><p>To launch the <em>Rolling Links</em> collection, adidas chose Palm Springs as the campaign backdrop, a setting known for its relaxed atmosphere and escape from the urban rush. Palm Springs perfectly reflects the ethos of the collection - a place where individuality, creativity, and leisure converge. The serenity and focus required in golf serve as a perfect counterbalance to the high-energy world of skateboarding.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
